(F) Relationship and Living Arrangement, 106 CMR 703.300;

(G) Residence, 106 CMR 703.340;

(H) Citizens, Noncitizens, and Canadian-born Indians, 106 CMR 703.400;

(I) Social Security Numbers, 106 CMR 701.230; and

(J) Cooperation with Child Support Enforcement Efforts, 106 CMR 703.500.

In order to receive EAEDC, an applicant or client must meet all of the applicable eligibility requirements. These requirements are both nonfinancial or financial.

The nonfinancial requirements for EAEDC eligibility are:

(A) Elderly - 65 Years of Age or Older, 106 CMR 703.600;

(B) Disabled, 106 CMR 703.191;

(C) Participant in a Massachusetts Rehabilitation Commission Program, 106 CMR 703.610;

(D) Caring for the Disabled, 106 CMR 703.620;

