(D) Impact on TAFDC Benefits

(1) The assistance unit shall receive a supplemental payment when the FEP gross income less 20 percent and less the allowable dependent care deduction as provided in 106 CMR 704.275, is less than the TAFDC benefit that the assistance unit would have received, based on the size of the assistance unit and any other income. The amount of the supplemental payment is the result of the above calculation.

(2) The Individual Asset Account established for the participant is a noncountable asset for TAFDC until the participant receives the funds from the account after leaving FEP employment.

